A course for those who have never learnt Russian before. Provides basic knowledge and skills and familiarises the learners with the system of Russian grammar….
The topics of the course:
Introducing person
Colours
Countries, nationalities and languages
Family and relatives
Occupations
Numerals, phone numbers, address
Studies
My day. My week. 
My favourites
My country and hometown
Leisure time and hobbies.
The basic grammar:
	The gender of nouns
	Adjectives
Personal and possessive pronouns
Declension of nouns and adjectives (singular only)
Verb forms: present, past and future (imperfect only)Objectives/eesmärkid:  The overall aim of the course is to provide the student with basic knowledge of Russian and develop reading, and basic oral and writing skills.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After completing the course the student should be able to: - read and understand simple texts in Russian; - use the vocabulary and grammar covered during the course in everyday situations; - get into social contact (to greet, to say goodbye, to introduce oneself, to thank, to apologies etc.); - talk about family, home town, hobbies, day schedule;   - understand the basic structures of Russian grammar; - ask simple questions and answer them.
